      "body": "hehe, I only read the lines you shared in the description.\nJust went deeper.. the issue isn't the test case; it clears the available coins right before start, so available coins shouldn't be compounding across loop iterations. The problem is inside `CoinsResult::Clear`:\n```c++\nvoid CoinsResult::Clear() {\n    coins.clear();\n}\n```\nWe are missing to clear the other two cached fields `total_amount` and `total_effective_amount`. That should fix the issue.\n\n```diff\nvoid CoinsResult::Clear() {\n     coins.clear();\n+    total_amount = 0;\n+    total_effective_amount = std::nullopt;\n }\n```",
      "user": {
        "login": "furszy",
        "id": 5377650,
        "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUzNzc2NTA=",
